| Overview            = The Imperial Starfleet is the primary armed service of the Skrull Empire. It is a force with 1000s of warships and fleets of varying sizes, some of which have 100s of warships.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 96}}{{r|Silver Surfer Vol 3 5}} {{r|Silver Surfer Vol 3 25}}{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1|8}} The supreme commander of the Imperial Starfleet is the emperor (or empress) of the Skrull Empire. Individual fleets and armadas are led by Generals,{{r|Avengers Vol 1 258|260}} Commandants,{{r|Avengers Vol 1 96}} and Grand Commanders.{{r|Secret Invasion: War of Kings Vol 1 1}} When the Skrull empire is divided, the various fleets are controlled by governors, warlords, and independent generals.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 258|260}}{{r|Annihilation: Super-Skrull Vol 1 1}}{{r|Avengers Vol 5 18}} 

It has a wide variety of warships types, including; Frigates,{{r|Avengers Vol 1 94}} [[Bird of Prey (Skrulls)|Birds of Prey]],{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 383}} Cruisers,{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 358}} Battlecruisers,{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 256}} Dreadnoughts,{{r|Annihilation: Super-Skrull Vol 1 1}} and Battleships{{r|Secret Invasion: Inhumans Vol 1|2}}. At the low end in size and capability are ships the size of two-story or multi-story Terran houses, the ([[Skrull Saucers|Saucers]] and [[Skrull Deathship|Deathships]]). They possess city-sized [[Skrull Battleship|capital ships]] that are a mile long or the size of mountains.{{r|Young Avengers Vol 1 12}}{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 6}}{{r|Nova Vol 4 18}} In the Skrull fleet the largest and most powerful warships are the [[Skrull War World|Destructor-class]], planetoid-sized warships.{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 358|359}} 

Warships of incredible power, with a saucer the size of a two-story Terran house being able to destroy a city with a blast from a single concentrated beam. That had the force of a megaton nuclear blast, powerful enough to the topple the peaks of Himalayan mountains as if they were castles made of sand.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 94}} Skrull armadas have the ability to turn Earth-sized worlds into balls of hellfire with a single missile or shatter a gas giant planet with two missiles.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 94}}{{r|Runaways Vol 3 2}}{{r|Runaways Vol 3 12}} The fleet's most powerful weapon is one that can be carried by a single Skrull warship, that burns every planet in a solar system by detonating its star.{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Annual Vol 3 1}}
