| History                 = 
Near the end of the [[Kree-Skrull War]], the Skrulls sent an armada to conquer Earth. It was intercepted by the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]] and defeated. It's commandant [[Kalxor (Earth-616)|Kalxor]] then attempted to have Earth destroyed with a massively powerful nuclear weapon that would turn the world into cinder, which was intercepted by [[Clinton Barton (Earth-616)|Goliath]].{{r|Avengers Vol 1 96}} 

After Galactus devoured the Skrull throneworld, the Skrull empire fragmented into various factions. The space pirate [[Nebula (Earth-616)|Nebula]] invaded Skrull space with a mercenary army, but was finally defeated by the combined forces of the Skrull fleet commanded by general [[Zedrao (Earth-616)|Zedrao]] and the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]].{{r|Avengers Vol 1 258|260}}

During the Second Kree-Skrull War, the [[Norrin Radd (Earth-616)|Silver Surfer]] and the pirate fleet of [[Reptyl (Earth-616)|Reptyl]], fought alongside the Skrull armada in their war against the [[Kree]] and their allies the [[Badoon]]. The Skrull fleet was personally led by the warlord (and later empress) [[S'Byll (Earth-616)|S'Byll]]. Several battles were fought in the vicinity of [[Zenn-La]]{{r|Silver Surfer Vol 3 25|29}}

[[File:Skrull Battleship from New Warriors Vol 4 14 0001.jpg|thumb|250px|Armada in Terran Sky]]
A massive Skrull armada participated in the attempted Skrull conquest of Earth by [[Veranke (Earth-616)|Queen Veranke]] two decades later. Which attacked and seized control of the [[Peak VII|Peak]], landed troops, and waged battle across the planet. They were finally defeated by the combined forces of Earth's military forces (e.g. [[Strategic Homeland Intervention, Enforcement and Logistics Division (Earth-616)|SHIELD]]) and heroes (e.g. the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]], the [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]], and the [[Thunderbolts (Earth-616)|Thunderbolts]]).{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1|8}} The retreating remnants of the invasion fleet led by Grand Commander [[H'jke Jeeku (Earth-616)|H'jke Jeeku]] were destroyed by the pursuing [[Inhumans]].{{r|Secret Invasion: War of Kings Vol 1 1}}

During the [[Infinity (Event)|Builders War]], the Skrull warlords united under [[Kl'rt (Earth-616)|Kl'rt]] the Super-Skrull who was now one of the warlords. Under his leadership, they joined the inter-galactic [[Galactic Council (Earth-616)|War Council]] and contributed their fleets to the fight against the [[Builders]].{{r|Avengers Vol 5 18}} Which participated in various space battles, alongside the fleets of the [[Shi'ar (Race)|Shi'ar]], [[Kree]], [[Spartax (Race)|Spartax]], [[Brood (Race)|Brood]], and [[Annihilation Wave]], and the Earth's heroes (the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]]).{{r|Infinity Vol 1 2|5}} After the defeat of the Builders, the combined alien fleet assisted the Avengers in liberating Earth from [[Thanos (Earth-616)|Thanos]] and his [[Black Order (Earth-616)|Black Order]].{{r|Infinity #6}}

==Technology==
The Skrullian warships possess various technologies, including:
*'''Intergalactic Warp Drives:''' Which give them the ability to travel intergalactic distances (millions of light years) within seconds or minutes via sub-space.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 94}}
* '''Intergalactic Sub-Space Communications:''' Nearly instantaneous.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 258}}
* '''Cloaking Technology:''' Which makes their vessels invisible to both radar and vision.{{r|Venom: First Host Vol 1 3}}{{r|Secret Invasion 6}}{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 357}}
* '''Anti-Cloaking Scanners'''{{r|Runaways Vol 2 8}}
* '''Teleportation:''' Capable of teleporting individuals or groups from orbit to a planet's surface and vice versa.{{r|Force Works Vol 1 13}}
* '''Brain-Wave Tracking System:''' Giving them the ability to locate & track a target on a planet from orbit.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 94}}
* '''Force Fields'''{{r|Iron Man: Director of S.H.I.E.L.D. Vol 1 35}}{{r|Secret Invasion: War of Kings Vol 1 1}}{{r|Thunderbolts Vol 1 123}}
* '''Deep Space Scanners:''' Which can scan in extreme detail what is happening in another world, 10s of thousands of light-years away.{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 262}}

==Weapons==
Skrullian warships are equipped with the following types of weapon systems:
* '''Thermonutron Planet-Killer Missiles:''' Fired from [[Skrull Battleship|Battleships]], two of which can end all life within minutes on a world and cause a chain reaction that shatters a gas giant in a few hours.{{r|Runaways Vol 3 2}}{{r|Runaways Vol 3 12}}
* '''Star-Killer Weapons:''' Fired from battleships, a large silvery sphere that when it is near the star's corona, it detonates the star resulting in every world in the solar system burning within a few light minutes.{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Annual Vol 3 1}}
* '''Fighters:''' Ranging in size from automobile-sized to heavy jet fighter-sized.{{r|Annihilation: Super-Skrull Vol 1 1}}{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 383}}{{r|Iron Man: Director of S.H.I.E.L.D. Vol 1 35}}
* '''Torpedoes:''' Photon and/or Ion torpedoes{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 206}}{{r|Nova Vol 1 25}}
* '''Beam Cannons/Guns:''' Energy Type (Photon, Maser, Disintegration, and/or Neutrino), Coherent Beam and/or Pulse Beam.{{r|Captain Marvel Vol 1 2}}{{r|Marvel Premiere Vol 1 35}}{{r|Avengers Vol 1 96}}{{r|Silver Surfer Vol 3 6}}{{r|Thunderbolts Vol 1 123}}
* '''Tactical Missiles:''' Used in space combat, to attack surface targets, etc.{{r|Avengers Vol 1 96}}{{r|X-Men Vol 3 29}}
